<p>Negotiators at the UN COP30 climate summit in Belém, Brazil, split on Friday after the host released a latest draft agreement that removed references to phasing out fossil fuels [thehindu.com#1][dw.com#2][ndtv.com#1][theglobeandmail.com#1]. European countries and more than 30 nations criticized the text, while oil-producing states were accused of resisting any phaseout mention; COP30 president André Corrêa do Lago urged delegates to find consensus [ndtv.com#1][dw.com#1][firstpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][michaelwest.com.au#1][mercopress.com#1]. The talks, due to end Friday, may run over after a fire earlier delayed proceedings [michaelwest.com.au#1][ndtv.com#1][mercopress.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/iSRPeYMh0sJyZnayRnwCymZ3vhzPuMXsKKMehsnc5gbuw2X6riLGrQ5nXivll6NehVfsVkUZZrzKXkKtqIP3KqpTQDHqL4ikOseaYcZwzo26DZNeB-Rc31Je-Ja0M3QR50qWB3Uc_Pe7hGt-zdz8CikZpChSbRr9oJO_F64hwgBN9XxjIM-BcBgL_GSgeiztRPtfkTGanSy-8ENYmRZQpPrqkt_SdgTabbZOCthaU2h0peMuJHivlnF5LfwFdQmyN3ve6rVENP5Zhgixmg' alt='Activists participate in a demonstration to transition away from fossil fuels outside the venue for the COP30 UN Climate Summit on Wednesday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Draft omission: Brazil’s latest draft, released before dawn, dropped earlier options on fossil fuels, leaving no explicit pathway on moving away from coal, oil and gas [michaelwest.com.au#1][dw.com#2][thehindu.com#1]</li><li>Pushback grows: Over 30 countries objected and the European Union rejected the draft, saying a phaseout path must be included [dw.com#1][ndtv.com#1]</li><li>Producer resistance: Oil- and gas-producing nations have resisted explicit phaseout language, with reports naming Russia, India and Saudi Arabia as blockers [firstpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]</li><li>Unity appeal: COP30 president André Corrêa do Lago urged delegates to reach consensus as the summit aimed to finish Friday evening [michaelwest.com.au#1][mercopress.com#1]</li><li>Beyond fuels: Negotiations also focus on finance for vulnerable countries and strengthening national climate plans [theglobeandmail.com#1][dw.com#2]</li></ul><blockquote>This cannot be an agenda that divides us. - André Corrêa do Lago</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>COP30 presidency (Brazil): The host urges countries to find unity and consensus to land a deal in the final hours [michaelwest.com.au#1][mercopress.com#1] (<a href='https://michaelwest.com.au/cop30-host-urges-unity-ahead-of-fossil-fuels-showdown/'>Michael West Media; MercoPress</a>)</li><li>European Union: EU members reject the draft that omits fossil-fuel phaseout language [ndtv.com#1] (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/nations-at-odds-over-fossil-fuels-as-cop30-draws-to-a-close-9677095#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li><li>Panama negotiators: Warn the talks are on the verge of collapse and risk “becoming a clown show” if the causes of the crisis aren’t named [theglobeandmail.com#1][michaelwest.com.au#1] (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-cop30-un-climate-talks-proposals-fossil-fuels/'>The Globe and Mail; Michael West Media</a>)</li><li>Oil-producing nations: Countries including Russia, India and Saudi Arabia are reported to be blocking references to a phaseout [straitstimes.com#1][firstpost.com#1] (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/cop30-climate-deal-under-threat-as-nations-clash-over-fossil-fuels'>The Straits Times; Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Environmental groups and activists: Call on delegates to move away from oil, gas and coal [michaelwest.com.au#1] (<a href='https://michaelwest.com.au/cop30-host-urges-unity-ahead-of-fossil-fuels-showdown/'>Michael West Media</a>)</li><li>Observers/analysts: Note the public row may also be a negotiating tactic as the summit nears its end [bbc.com#1] (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c0q5ewew4geo'>BBC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/nations-at-odds-over-fossil-fuels-as-cop30-draws-to-a-close-9677095#